theorem closure_frontier_eq_closure_iff_empty_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    (A : Set X) :
    closure (frontier A) = closure A ↔ interior A = (∅ : Set X) := by
  constructor
  · intro hEq
    -- `frontier A` is closed, so its closure is itself.
    have hClosedFront : IsClosed (frontier A) := frontier_isClosed (X := X) (A := A)
    have hClFront : closure (frontier A) = frontier A := hClosedFront.closure_eq
    -- Hence `frontier A = closure A`.
    have hFrontEq : frontier A = closure A := by
      simpa [hClFront] using hEq
    -- But `frontier A = closure A \ interior A`.
    have hFrontDef :
        frontier A = closure A \ interior A :=
      frontier_eq_closure_diff_interior (X := X) (A := A)
    -- Combine the two equalities.
    have hEquality : closure A = closure A \ interior A := by
      simpa [hFrontEq] using hFrontDef
    -- Show that `interior A` is empty.
    have hIntEmpty : interior A = (∅ : Set X) := by
      by_contra hNonEmpty
      rcases (Set.nonempty_iff_ne_empty).mpr hNonEmpty with ⟨x, hxInt⟩
      have hxClos : x ∈ closure A :=
        subset_closure (interior_subset hxInt)
      -- Using `hEquality`, rewrite membership in `closure A`.
      have hxDiff : x ∈ closure A \ interior A := by
        simpa [hEquality] using hxClos
      exact (hxDiff.2 hxInt).elim
    exact hIntEmpty
  · intro hIntEmpty
    -- If `interior A = ∅`, then `frontier A = closure A`.
    have hFrontEq : frontier A = closure A :=
      frontier_eq_closure_of_empty_interior (A := A) hIntEmpty
    -- Since `frontier A` is closed, its closure is itself.
    have hClosedFront : IsClosed (frontier A) := frontier_isClosed (X := X) (A := A)
    have hClFront : closure (frontier A) = frontier A := hClosedFront.closure_eq
    -- Combine the equalities.
    simpa [hFrontEq, hClFront]

theorem frontier_inter_interior_compl_eq_empty
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    frontier (A : Set X) ∩ interior (Aᶜ) = (∅ : Set X) := by
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · intro x hx
    have hxFront : x ∈ frontier A := hx.1
    have hxIntComp : x ∈ interior (Aᶜ) := hx.2
    -- `interior (Aᶜ)` is the complement of `closure A`
    have hIntEq : interior (Aᶜ : Set X) = (closure A)ᶜ :=
      interior_compl_eq_compl_closure (A := A)
    have hxNotClosure : x ∉ closure A := by
      have : x ∈ (closure A)ᶜ := by
        simpa [hIntEq] using hxIntComp
      exact this
    have hxClosure : x ∈ closure A := hxFront.1
    have hFalse : False := hxNotClosure hxClosure
    exact False.elim hFalse
  · exact Set.empty_subset _
